Q5Create Customer table using NOT NULL, CHECK and DEFAULT constraints. 
CREATE TABLE Customer2 ( 
CustID INT PRIMARY KEY, 
Name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, 
Age INT CHECK (Age >= 18), 
City VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'Pune' 
); 
INSERT INTO Customer2 
VALUES (1, 'Amit', 25, 'Mumbai'); 
Note: 
This will give error (correct behavior): 
INSERT INTO Customer2 
VALUES (2, NULL, 15, 'Delhi'); 
Because: 
• Name cannot be NULL 
• Age must be ≥ 18 
